                                                                                                               Three-way GHCL recast
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	Mumbai, March 24: Gujarat Heavy Chemicals Ltd (GHCL) will demerge its business into three separate entities  soda ash, retail, and home textiles.         
	GHCLs retail and home textile businesses will be transferred to two separate wholly owned subsidiaries.         
	The proposed retail entity will handle Indian and UK ventures. The company plans to shift the business of the UK-based Rosebys to the proposed retail subsidiary. GHCL acquired Rosebys in 2006.        
	The restructuring will provide enhanced financial flexibility to the businesses to independently raise resources for their growth and unlock potential valuations for shareholders, said chairman Sanjay Dalmia.         
	The companys retail products are expected to be launched early next quarter.        
	GHCL expects the home textiles entity to become one of the strongest sourcing power houses in the world. The company manages the largest home textiles retail chain in the UK with more than 300 stores.                                                                                                                                                
